commit.message: Remove try-except constructs needed for Python 2

Replace deprecated multi_db option by databases

The multi_db attribute is deprecated since Django 2.2, hence we replace it by the new databases option.
See https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/3.0/topics/testing/tools/#django.test.TransactionTestCase.multi_db

This entails that we also drop support for Django 1.11 and Python 3.4.

Closes #104

Split up documentation into chapters

Our documentation has grown over time. From only a few
usage instructions in the README to mainly a single page of
user guide, with only Contributing being a separate chapter.
Splitting up will make consumption easier, and it will
accommodate adding new content easily and properly.

Fix Travis CI validation complaints

Run deploy job really only when a tag is pushed

Remove Lockfile for pipenv

We only want easy development, not packaging
Modernize test setup (Tox, Travis, drop Python 2.7)
Updated docs' fixture decorator warning to be less foreboding.
Fix for #92 to avoid scenario-specific fixtures running on other scenarios
Use list syntax for INSTALLED_APPS in docs

Update contributing docs, remove dev requirements

Add clean target to Tox configuration
Remove now unsupported Django 2.0 from test matrix

Enable messages context processor in test project

Replace old-style MIDDLEWARE_CLASSES by MIDDLEWARE (overdue!)

Add SecurityMiddleware, remove SessionAuthenticationMiddleware

Use list syntax for INSTALLED_APPS and MIDDLEWARE, finally

As required by Django 2.2
Link docs badge to build overview page
Add badge for docs build, use Shields.io badge for Gitter
